92
00:10:52,631 --> 00:10:54,592
And we use this funding to supplement

93
00:10:56,013 --> 00:11:01,538
our offering of reduced tuition for families that qualify as low or moderate income.

94
00:11:02,038 --> 00:11:18,291
And this funding allows us to assist in tuition for more families, or if we don't have more families who qualify, then assist families more so we can help them deeper cut their tuition costs for the afterschool program.

95
00:11:18,972 --> 00:11:21,394
The afterschool program is a self-sustaining program.

96
00:11:21,554 --> 00:11:22,575
It's tuition-based,

97
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:26,216
So all of our costs are paid for by the incoming tuitions.

98
00:11:26,667 --> 00:11:36,412
So the costs include the payment for staffs, supplies, and our incidentals like the cell phones that we need to use and walkie talkies, those sorts of things.

99
00:11:36,812 --> 00:11:44,276
So as long as our costs are covered by the tuitions, we keep it as close as we can to make it as affordable as we can for families.

100
00:11:44,696 --> 00:11:51,180
But as we know, there are still several families that can't afford the full tuition that we have, despite the fact that we keep it as low as we can.

101
00:11:51,620 --> 00:11:55,802
So this help coming from CDBG has really helped a lot of families

102
00:11:56,260 --> 00:12:01,283
We've helped an average of 14 to 15 students over the last several years, every year.

103
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:05,706
This year, we stopped taking vouchers from the state.

104
00:12:06,107 --> 00:12:15,993
So this was very helpful for us to help families who had qualified for vouchers so that they didn't lose the tuition amounts that they had paid in the past with their vouchers.

105
00:12:16,253 --> 00:12:22,958
But we were also able to offer financial assistance to more families who didn't qualify for voucher for one reason or another.

106
00:12:23,587 --> 00:12:25,088
So we will continue to do that.

107
00:12:25,929 --> 00:12:26,810
I've set a goal.

108
00:12:27,951 --> 00:12:33,976
Right now we have about 360 students enrolled in our after school program and 10% only have

109
00:12:36,697 --> 00:12:39,558
submitted paperwork to qualify for financial assistance.

110
00:12:40,118 --> 00:12:44,079
And I think that doesn't sound quite right.

111
00:12:44,179 --> 00:12:55,423
So I've made a commitment to do a really concerted effort on educating families to, in case it's a stigma problem, and to remove stigma for applying for financial assistance if they qualify.

112
00:12:56,237 --> 00:13:01,158
or in case families think they can't even apply to the after-school program because they think they can't afford it.

113
00:13:01,258 --> 00:13:12,802
So I'm doing a kind of concerted outreach effort this May to try and reach families to let them know what they qualify for and make sure that everybody's really informed about what their options are.

114
00:13:13,942 --> 00:13:14,462
But thank you.

115
00:13:14,482 --> 00:13:19,003
We wouldn't be able to do that without the help from CDBG, so we really very much appreciate it.

116
00:13:21,984 --> 00:13:22,284
Thank you.

117
00:13:22,404 --> 00:13:25,105
Any questions for after-school program?

118
00:13:26,345 --> 00:13:27,868
