00:13:30,895 --> 00:13:33,159
Crossman from the West Medford Community Center.

120
00:13:34,953 --> 00:13:38,634
Hi, thank you for allowing us to present today.

121
00:13:38,654 --> 00:13:56,938
I've been with the center going on a year and a half now, but we have received this funding for many years and we are requesting the 21,000 to support our elder services director, the role.

122
00:13:58,218 --> 00:14:04,320
This year we'd like to offer our seniors an opportunity for day trips.

123
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:13,143
And so we, our program is a place where seniors can find social and intellectual interactions.

124
00:14:14,863 --> 00:14:26,307
And we are our target population are the seniors in Medford who are still living at home but would benefit from the stimulation that comes with ongoing social interaction.

125
00:14:28,401 --> 00:14:41,792
We found that the AARP's 2021 Home and Community Preference Survey said that one in four adults aged 50 plus report feeling less connected to their community since the COVID-19 outbreak.

126
00:14:41,932 --> 00:14:50,779
And so a lot of our focus this year is on community, bringing our seniors together to reduce isolation, reduce the opportunities

127
00:14:51,580 --> 00:15:08,469
for depression, improve feelings of belonging, trust, and security, being that they're going to feel healthier and that they'll feel more connected to their community and more inclined to take action to improve their own health, stay in their own homes.

128
00:15:09,389 --> 00:15:37,195
Um, we are looking this year to have meaningful, intentional volunteer and leadership opportunities for our seniors, which they've already taken the role on, um, stronger relationships with our city, um, in our city networks, making our networks that much larger as we work to be a resiliency hub ourselves, um, and having creative, social, recreational, cultural, and physical activities and guest speakers and events to support our seniors.

129
00:15:40,728 --> 00:15:41,328
Thank you, Lisa.

130
00:15:41,728 --> 00:15:42,789
Any questions from the council?

131
00:15:44,569 --> 00:15:45,950
